    {
        "content": "<p>I suspect Lean will not unfold that <code>f</code> unless explicitly asked (which would explain the error because you defined <code>f</code> but didn't prove any theorems about it). Probably <code>unfold f</code> or <code>simp [f]</code> will enable <code>continuity</code> but there might be tricks like <code>continuity [f]</code> (not sure, this is not a tactic I use much and I'm not at lean right now)</p>",
        "id": 479150429,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1730050188
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or changing <code>def f</code> to <code>abbrev f</code> (which aesop will unfold) would also probably work</p>",
        "id": 479150546,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1730050286
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thank you. <code>unfold f</code> worked.</p>",
        "id": 479151447,
        "sender_full_name": "Duncan Skahan",
        "timestamp": 1730051081
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, you'll likely prefer to use <code>fun_prop</code> instead of <code>continuity</code>.</p>",
